$interpreted: Senior Cleric: ...We're so fortunate that the Holy Maiden's powers have been restored. The throne won't dare make a move against the Shrine.
Senior Cleric: Your believers have also gradually returned.
Misa: I don't want to cause Her Majesty any trouble. My...*cough*...powers will be used to help the people.
Senior Cleric: Indeed. This is the good fortune of the desert.
Senior Cleric: But where did you find your medicine? If it runs out again...
Misa: ...He will hide in the dark...watching.
Misa: If he feels I have done well, he will bring more.
Senior Cleric: Ah, the garland, its color has faded. It must have been hanging for too long.
Senior Cleric: There are words written on it...
Senior Cleric: "Congratulations to our Misa, for becoming the Holy Maiden. Welcome back."
Misa: I'm so stupid for saying such hurtful words.
Misa: Forgive me, I was wrong. All of you, I am sorry...
